Kaveel Singh, News24The pooch after he had been rescued Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Paramedics rescued a distressed dog south of Johannesburg on Thursday after it was found beneath a prefabricated classroom at a school in Edenpark. &ldquo;When ER24 paramedics, along with another service, arrived on the scene, they found the dog cowering deep beneath one of the classrooms,&rdquo; ER24 spokesperson Russel Meiring said. Meiring said members of the public alerted ER24 to the incident after they found the dog lying underneath the classroom.&ldquo;Paramedics were informed that the animal had been beneath the building for at least three days. One of the ER24 paramedics was able to crawl beneath the building and slowly coax the animal out.&rdquo;Meiring said that once the dog was brought to safety, paramedics assessed and treated her before she was handed over to Kibler Park Vet for further treatment.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.